{"id": "duc04-testb-23:7#22", "contents": "The summit brought together heads of state and government from Latin America, Spain, and Portugal to explore measures to mitigate the financial turmoil that has already devastated Asia and Russia. Latin American leaders must assess the need for unpopular reforms, including austerity packages, which risk social unrest and political upheaval. A joint declaration will be signed on Sunday, calling on the international community to promote stability in international financial markets and support sustained economic growth. Diplomats reported consensus on the final statement, which emphasizes the need for regulatory systems to control speculators and prevent crises."}
